---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Mermaid from '../../components/Mermaid.astro';
---

<Layout title="Architecture" description="Monorepo layout, two paths, IPC seam, data flow.">
  <h1>Architecture</h1>

  <h2>Monorepo layout</h2>
  <pre><code>{`needle/
  apps/
    desktop/     @needle/desktop — Electron + Vite + React
    handbook/    @needle/handbook — Astro static site (this)
  packages/
    domain/      @needle/domain — types, validation, rules
    contract/    @needle/contract — IPC/API shapes
    config/      @needle/config — shared tsconfig base
  docs/          product + architecture markdown
  design/        design system docs
  memory/        context + decisions log`}</code></pre>

  <h2>Two paths, one shared core</h2>
  <Mermaid
    chart={`flowchart TB
    subgraph core [Shared core]
      D[packages/domain]
      C[packages/contract]
    end
    subgraph pathA [Path A — Mac]
      DT[apps/desktop]
      SQL[(SQLite local)]
    end
    subgraph pathB [Path B — Cloud]
      SV[apps/server planned]
      WB[apps/web planned]
      PG[(Postgres)]
    end
    core --> DT
    core --> SV
    DT --> SQL
    SV --> PG
    DT -. sync adapter later .-> SV`}
  />

  <ul>
    <li><strong>Path A</strong> — macOS standalone, local-first SQLite, never blocked on backend</li>
    <li><strong>Path B</strong> — NestJS + Postgres + web/mobile, parallel track</li>
    <li><strong>Bridge</strong> — deferred sync adapter; same domain model prevents divergence</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Electron process boundaries</h2>
  <table>
    <thead><tr><th>Context</th><th>Role</th><th>Rules</th></tr></thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr><td><code>main/</code></td><td>App lifecycle, IPC, SQLite, AI, native APIs</td><td>Node only</td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>preload/</code></td><td><code>contextBridge</code> → <code>window.api</code></td><td>Thin bridge</td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>renderer/</code></td><td>React UI</td><td>No Node; IPC only</td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>shared/</code> (packages)</td><td>Types, pure helpers</td><td>No Node/DOM</td></tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>

  <h2>IPC seam (connect later)</h2>
  <p>
    Renderer talks only via <code>window.api</code>. To add cloud sync later, swap what main does
    behind handlers (API + cache vs SQLite-only) — renderer unchanged. Contracts live in
    <code>@needle/contract</code>, evolving from ipc-contracts.
  </p>

  <Mermaid
    chart={`sequenceDiagram
    participant R as Renderer
    participant P as Preload
    participant M as Main IPC handler
    participant S as SQLite / API
    R->>P: window.api.tasks.list()
    P->>M: ipcMain.handle
    M->>S: query or fetch
    S-->>M: data
    M-->>P: typed response
    P-->>R: render`}
  />

  <h2>Transport-agnostic UI (future)</h2>
  <p>
    Planned <code>packages/ui-web</code> components receive data + callbacks — same components on
    desktop (via IPC-backed props) and web (via api-client).
  </p>

  <p><a href="/infra/">Infra 101 →</a> · <a href="/reference/docs/v2/monorepo-migration-plan/">Migration plan</a></p>
</Layout>
